		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top" id="forumSubject">Songs to keep in the forn of yer book...<br clear="all" /><script type="text/javascript">document.title = document.title + ": Thread: Songs to keep in the forn of yer book...";</script>
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Wed, Aug 22nd 4:42 PM2001 </span><span class="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a href="/db/classes.html?class=4&mid=99851293930994&post=1"><a class="sm" href="/db/classes.html?class=4&mid=99851293930994&num=0&post=1&replyto=99851293930994"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=99851293930994></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span class="notbold">By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></a><b><span id=></span></b>
		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Default [2.33]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Anonymous&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Hallo all. Twynk Coppertop (formerly Twynk Eltoes) of Tunare. Decided to impart a wee bit of info fer tha young ones of our humble class. <br /><br />#1 the only 2 stats you should focus on when creating/growing yer bard are Dex and Cha. Dex will help in casting yer songs tha first time everytime, which makes it easier to twist. Cha makes yer songs much more effective, especially any that deal with charming or mezzing. I play my bard very similiar to an enchanter with armor and twin blades. I charm every add that comes with the pull, sick it on whoever is the main kill, and twist anthem, warmth, and fufil's. In this way, I have a pet doing damage to the central mob, I am keeping a DoT on it, I have the entire party buffed with str, haste, sv. cold, ac, and damage shield. When fighting necromancers and tha like, I switch from warmth to vitality, as it has a chance with every cast to remove disease effects, i.e. 90% of those nasty little necro DoTs! if the party pulls 3 mobs, then I charm one, and make it fight the 3rd mob while everyone else focuses on the first mob. By doing this, by the time we are ready to fight either mob 2 or 3, they are both usually well over half-dead! Feel free at anytime ya see me wanderin' around Tunare ta give me a holler and strike up a conversation. I don't play much anymore due to a hectic RL schedule, but (and no I'm not trying to brag, I am merely stating a fact) you can ask anyone of tha hunerd's of people that know ole Twynk, and they will be sure ta tell yas that I know m'stuff. I have learned that the only 2 classes that can save a parties arse anywhere as effective as a bard can is a cleric, or a good enchanter. We can mez, charm, heal, buff, debuff, DoT, DD, snare, breathe water, levitate, clarity, shadow step tha whole party, AoE fear, and many other things, and thats only up to lvl 31!! Jack of all trades, master of none. Well, except perhaps escape. Nobody, and I mean nobody, can haul-arse lika well trained bard ;)<br />Hope ya gain'd a wee bit o'knowledge, and like I said, feel free ta holler at me in game.<br /><br />Twynk Coppertop (though many remember me as Twynk Eltoes er simply Twynk)<br />Bard of 33rd Song<br />The Progeny Sentinels &lt;Tunarian Sect&gt; <br /><br />Bristlebane pad yer pockets eternally m'friends!</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td></tr></table>
